Extracting bread matrix for singleR class

Source: R/sandwichMethods.R
bread.singleR.Rd

Extracting bread matrix for singleR class

Usage

# S3 method for singleR
bread(object, ...)

Arguments

object

an object representing a fitted model.

...

additional optional arguments passed to the following functions:

  • stats::vcov -- for extracting "the usual" variance-covariance matrix, vcov.singleR has one additional argument type with values "Fisher" "observedInform", defaults to the one specified in controlPopVar specified in call for object.

Value

A bread matrix, i.e. a hessian based estimation of variance-covariance matrix scaled by degrees of freedom.

See also

sandwich::bread() controlPopVar()

Author

Piotr Chlebicki, Maciej Beręsewicz

An S3class for sandwich::bread to handle singleR objects. This function was developed based on sandwich:::bread.glm

Examples

Model <- estimatePopsize(
formula = capture ~ ., 
data = netherlandsimmigrant, 
model = ztpoisson, 
method = "IRLS")
sandwich::bread(Model)
